cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper discusses privacy-preserving mechanisms for spatiotemporal events, which involves both location and time information. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper proposes a new privacy metric, which involves indistinguishability-based privacy, suggesting that it may also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CY).
